  "prompt": "How one can apply for IIMs after cat results?",
  "response": "After the CAT results are announced, candidates who wish to apply for admission to the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) need to follow a specific process. Here is a general outline of the steps involved:\n\n1. **Check Eligibility:**\n   Ensure that you meet the eligibility criteria for the specific IIM and program you are interested in. This usually includes a minimum CAT percentile, academic qualifications, and other criteria.\n\n2. **Apply for Shortlisting:**\n   Most IIMs automatically consider candidates who have taken the CAT exam for their programs. You do not need to apply separately to each IIM for shortlisting. However, some IIMs may require candidates to fill out a detailed application form or provide additional information.\n\n3. **Shortlisting for WAT/GD-PI:**\n   Based on your CAT score and other criteria (such as academic performance, work experience, diversity factors), IIMs will shortlist candidates for the next stage of the admission process, which typically includes a Written Ability Test (WAT), Group Discussion (GD), and Personal Interview (PI).\n\n4. **Receive Shortlist Notification:**\n   If you are shortlisted, you will receive a notification from the respective IIM(s). This will include details about the next steps, including dates, venues, and other requirements for WAT/GD-PI.\n\n5. **Prepare and Attend WAT/GD-PI:**\n   Prepare for the WAT, GD, and PI by researching common topics, practicing writing, and honing your interview skills. Attend the WAT/GD-PI as per the schedule provided.\n\n6. **Submit Additional Documents:**\n   Some IIMs may require you to submit additional documents such as academic transcripts, certificates, and work experience proofs. Ensure you have all the required documents ready.\n\n7. **Final Selection:**\n   After the WAT/GD-PI process, IIMs will evaluate your performance in these activities along with your CAT score, academic background, work experience, and other factors to make the final admission decision.\n\n8. **Acceptance and Admission:**\n   If you are offered admission, you will receive an offer letter from the IIM. Follow the instructions provided in the offer letter to confirm your acceptance and complete the admission formalities, including payment of fees.\n\n9. **Waitlist and Multiple Offers:**\n   If you are waitlisted, keep an eye on updates from the IIM. Additionally, it is common for candidates to receive multiple offers from different IIMs. Carefully evaluate each offer before making your final decision.\n\n10. **Complete Admission Process:**\n    Once you accept an offer, complete any remaining admission process steps, such as attending orientation sessions and submitting final documents.\n\nRemember to keep track of deadlines and specific requirements for each IIM you are interested in, as these may vary.",
